 with spatula. Cover with cling wrap, refrigerate until set (approx. 30 min.)."},{"content":"Preheat broiler. Line a baking sheet with foil and lightly spray with non-stick oil."},{"content":"Cut firm polenta into long fingers (approx. 3 in. x ½ in.). Lightly spray tops of polenta with non-stick oil. Place under broiler for 3-5 minutes each side until crispy. Serve with marinara sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["The polenta can be prepared, refrigerated and cut in advance.","To make your own marinara: refer to the Marinara Dipping Sauce recipe in the Pizza collection."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 10m","75 pieces"]}